HARRISON, SAMUEL BEALEY – Volume IX (1861-1870)

	d. 23 July 1867 at Toronto, Ont.


ConfederationResponsible GovernmentSir John A. MacdonaldFrom the Red River Settlement to Manitoba (1812–70)Sir Wilfrid LaurierSir George-Étienne CartierSportsThe FeniansWomen in the DCB/DBCWinning the Right to VoteThe Charlottetown and Quebec Conferences of 1864Introductory Essays of the DCB/DBCThe AcadiansFor EducatorsExploring the ExplorersThe War of 1812 Canada’s Wartime Prime MinistersThe First World WarBack to top 















 

